/* gamedata-w7-button.mjs — The Button (W7 daily account-wide task/requirement checker), extracted
 * verbatim from N.js: the full 57-task table + the task-selection and requirement formulas.
 * GENERATED by a one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed); refresh after a major
 * patch.
 *
 * SCOPE — bonuses/minehead.mjs already owns Button_Bonuses/BUTTON_PER_TIME (the reward-per-press
 * table, buckets OptLacc[594] presses into 9 buckets of 5). THIS file is a different Button
 * mechanic entirely: which TASK is currently active (a rotating account-wide requirement like
 * "reach 1000 total STR"), found via the same `m._customBlock_Minehead` dispatcher.
 *
 * Button_Task(), N.js byte ~10921470, verbatim (OLA = OptionsListAccount; ButtonTasks.length=57):
 *   slot = round(OLA[594] - 100*floor(OLA[594]/100))        // OLA[594] mod 100
 *   raw  = CustomLists.Research[39][slot]                    // Research[39]: a 100-entry
 *                                                             // permutation of 0..99 (see
 *                                                             // gamedata-w7-research.mjs's header
 *                                                             // for the shared Ya.Research()
 *                                                             // literal this comes from — NOT
 *                                                             // re-exported there, only noted)
 *   return round(raw - 57*floor(raw/57))                     // raw mod ButtonTasks.length
 * i.e. the button-press counter (mod 100) indexes into a 100-long shuffle table, then folds mod
 * 57 into a valid BUTTON_TASKS index — a two-stage shuffle so consecutive presses don't cycle
 * tasks in a visibly linear order.
 *
 * Button_REQ(), N.js byte ~10921620, verbatim (task = BUTTON_TASKS[Button_Task()]):
 *   task.mode=="linear" ? ceil(task.threshold + OLA[594] * task.coeff)
 *   task.mode=="step"   ? ceil(task.threshold + OLA[594] / task.coeff)
 *   else ("exponent")   ? task.threshold * Math.pow(task.coeff, OLA[594])
 * NOTE: Button_REQ scales with the RAW total press count OLA[594] (not "presses since this task
 * was rolled") — the requirement climbs forever as you press more, regardless of which task is
 * currently showing. Transcribed as-is, not simplified; this looks unusual but is exactly what
 * the dispatcher does.
 *
 * BUTTON_TASKS — Ya.ButtonTasks()=function(){return[...]}, N.js byte 13973611 (`return[` at
 * 13973643..13978135). 57 rows, columns [desc, threshold, mode, coeff, flag]. `flag` (0/1,
 * verbatim) is not consumed by Button_Task/Button_REQ above — plausibly a "hard" vs "easy" UI
 * tag (spot-check: flag==1 rows are mostly slower/rarer mode=="linear"/"step" progress trackers
 * like statue levels and skill levels; flag==0 rows are mostly mode=="exponent" currency/stat
 * totals) — not confirmed by a dispatcher read, so left as a bare verbatim column rather than
 * asserted.
 * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

